article.headline: Alabama A&M 96, Alabama State 93 (OT)
article.story: MONTGOMERY, Ala. (AP) -- Marcus Young hit four free throws over the final 28 seconds in overtime, raising Alabama A&M to a 96-93 victory over Alabama State on Saturday night. Young's layup tied the game 83-83 with 4 seconds left in regulation play, sending both teams into overtime. The teams tied again 89-89 at the 1:31 mark in overtime on a free throw by Ricky Ricketts. A 3-pointer by Richard Lott with 3 seconds remaining put Alabama State within 3. Ricketts led the Bulldogs (11-10, 8-3 Southwestern Athletic Conference) with 28 points on 9-of-18 shooting. Obie Trotter added 20 points, Young had 18 and Joe Martin had 16. Martin also pulled down nine rebounds. Jermaine Smith was perfect in seven field goal attempts and hit eight of 11 from the foul line for Alabama State (11-9, 9-2). Alexander Oliver added 18 points, Kevin Spicer had 16 and Ralfeal Golden 15. Smith and Spicer combined for 23 rebounds for the Hornets, who dominated the boards 43-28. Alabama State led 47-44 at halftime.
